Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.57,0:00:40.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A museum? Isn't that a bit unusual for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.07,0:00:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you curious to see what he looks like?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.52,0:00:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he's a beautiful older man!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.37,0:00:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like Harrison Ford, John Lennon, or maybe Brad Pitt...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.69,0:00:53.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard he collects famous jewelry from all over the world and holds exhibitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.92,0:00:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I hear that you get to see the biggest black pearl in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.92,0:01:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the Black Star, the black pearl that is said to bring happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.45,0:01:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three steel crows in the dark of the night...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.06,0:02:01.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And two more beyond that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.07,0:02:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.30,0:02:05.34,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kaito Kuroba (17)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.94,0:02:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They've even got an armored vehicle ready...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.42,0:02:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the police for ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.80,0:02:09.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They've sure gone all-out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.54,0:02:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't, Master Kaito...{how do we want to handle this? -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.20,0:02:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have an uncomfortable feeling about this project...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.35,0:02:15.10,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kōnosuke Jii (61)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.49,0:02:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're cornered like before, and if something should ever happen to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.09,0:02:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I, as your steward, wouldn't be able to apologize to Tōichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} before his altar...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.04,0:02:28.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.45,0:02:31.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're always like this before a big project!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.24,0:02:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gimme a break, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.01,0:02:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.77,0:02:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Master Kaito...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.81,0:02:42.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, tonight I'm not the son of Tōichi Kuroba, the magician whom you served as steward for,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.26,0:02:46.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,nor am I Kaito, a second-year high school student.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.99,0:02:49.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who everybody's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.85,0:03:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A villain putting on a show.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.70,0:03:08.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Master Kaito...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.58,0:03:23.34,Title,,0,0,0,,SHIN'ICHI KUDŌ VS. KAITŌ KID\NGREAT DETECTIVES, ASSEMBLE!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.34,0:03:26.34,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ekoda High School
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:27.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Too easy. Way too easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.26,0:03:31.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The next job is a piece of cake that I could complete with the tip of my pinky...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.61,0:03:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Kid garners legions of fangirls!" That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.86,0:03:44.15,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Aoko Nakamori (17)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.81,0:03:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To hell with legions of fangirls!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:51.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To me, it's like he's {\i1}trying{\i0} to become the biggest loser in the universe!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.14,0:03:56.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.24,0:04:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like that dumb gumshoe of a dad you've got is ever gonna beat him or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.99,0:04:10.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.54,0:04:12.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.68,0:04:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.56,0:04:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.16,0:04:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An amazing phantom thief that can't be chained!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.64,0:04:26.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The final episode of Star Wars's gonna come out before that Inspector even comes {\i1}near{\i0} arresting him!{my god this is so dated}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.59,0:04:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up! Just because you look like Kid and can do some magic, you're always sticking up for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.55,0:04:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just abandons or returns everything he steals!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.60,0:04:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not being a gentleman—it's just smug!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.23,0:04:42.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.21,0:04:47.01,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Akako Koizumi (17)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.42,0:04:46.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's exactly {\i1}why{\i0} I like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.88,0:04:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's charmingly cute, like a mischievous little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.84,0:04:53.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Akako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! Akako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.29,0:04:58.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't let him deceive you! That guy's nothing but a criminal, and that's all there is to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.44,0:05:04.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, you saw on the news what Kid's after next, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.29,0:05:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you mean the old clock tower in front of the station?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.39,0:05:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! That belongs to everyone here in this town!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.09,0:05:15.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd have to be pretty awful to go and steal something like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.36,0:05:16.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I guess so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.47,0:05:21.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.05,0:05:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That clock tower is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.38,0:05:33.22,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Keiko Momoi (17)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.51,0:05:32.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But I heard the clock tower was going to be moved somewhere else soon anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.28,0:05:34.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's going to be used as a landmark for some theme park...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.54,0:05:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.01,0:05:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everybody was saying that if it's gotta go, it might as well be taken away by Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.39,0:05:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two wrongs don't make a right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.76,0:05:46.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I don't know what you're up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.74,0:05:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I really think you should call off the job you're planning to carry out this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.33,0:05:54.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How many times do I gotta tell you? I'm not Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.66,0:05:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"When the 20,000th song is sung from the historic tower whence it carries,"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.43,0:06:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"the demon of light will fly from the east and strike down the sinner in white, for whom the bell tolls disaster."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.36,0:06:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that supposed to be my fortune or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.44,0:06:11.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no mere fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.22,0:06:14.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a prophecy imparted to me by the devil, Lucifer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.03,0:06:15.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,L-Luci—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.01,0:06:19.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The day that clock sounds its bell for the 20,000th time is the night
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.28,0:06:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that you warned you'll be carrying out your deed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.76,0:06:25.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whether or not you believe me is up to you, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.32,0:06:40.62,Signs,,0,0,0,,Clock Tower
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.62,0:06:43.58,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ginzō Nakamori (41)\NMetro Police Investigation Division 2 Inspector
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.00,0:06:48.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,All patrol cars and helicopters around the clock tower:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.11,0:06:51.69,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Report any sightings of suspicious people to me immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.69,0:06:54.42,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}To the guards in each block of the tower:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.42,0:06:57.45,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nobody gets through without my explicit approval!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.45,0:07:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guard the post that you're assigned to with your entire heart and soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.19,0:07:02.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Inspector Nakamori...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.89,0:07:04.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is Kid really going to show up?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.38,0:07:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His warning went like this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.49,0:07:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"On Saturday night, underneath the full moon, I will appear before you at the stroke of midnight"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"to take the towering clock from your side."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.77,0:07:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Kaitō Kid."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.37,0:07:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you'd need a crane to steal something that big...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.18,0:07:21.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.55,0:07:23.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he says he's gonna steal it, he's gonna steal it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.87,0:07:25.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hands of the clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.08,0:07:31.17,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Futoshi Takarada (53)\NClock Tower Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.64,0:07:29.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,50 years ago, as mayor, my father spent a fortune
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.76,0:07:36.24,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,to have them crafted by a famous clockmaker overseas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.24,0:07:39.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hour hand of the clock, along with the signature of the designer,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.49,0:07:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,has several large diamonds embedded in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.23,0:07:44.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is a highly valued work of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.84,0:07:47.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd bank on {\i1}those{\i0} being what he's after.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.89,0:07:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why'd you let the owner through?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.11,0:07:51.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.16,0:07:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He insisted that he wanted to check out the security conditions himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.79,0:07:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sure hope you checked thoroughly whether he is really the owner?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.05,0:07:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.75,0:08:01.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever you do...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.94,0:08:04.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever you do, please protect it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.40,0:08:11.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I inherited this clock tower from my late father,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.36,0:08:15.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so please protect it from the clutches of that petty thief and his ridiculous heist notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.14,0:08:17.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll get it done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.11,0:08:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.82,0:08:21.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:25.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen Police Superintendent Hakuba's son Saguru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} around lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.15,0:08:31.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said something about having some unfinished case to take care of and went back to London.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.59,0:08:34.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We sure could've used his help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.07,0:08:35.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.00,0:08:36.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.27,0:08:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{What makes you think we can count on that costume-wearing freak every time?!}We can't depend on that costume-wearing freak every freaking time!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.09,0:08:50.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only 28 minutes and 30 seconds until the promised time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.17,0:08:51.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.19,0:09:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, Sergeant Yōichi Sensui from Ekoda, 27 and single...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.65,0:09:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to borrow your name and face for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.41,0:09:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.29,0:09:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's an amazing crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.13,0:09:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sir! How's everything inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.36,0:09:24.91,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Sujio Hosokawa (32)\NSubordinate of Takarada
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.18,0:09:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.04,0:09:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not even an ant could sneak through.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.94,0:09:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.63,0:09:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if everything is okay on the amusement park's side...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.10,0:09:32.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said that if we don't start transportation by tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.45,0:09:34.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it'll be too late to have the tower ready for opening day,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.15,0:09:37.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and they'll have to cancel the purchase!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.15,0:09:43.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if Kid steals the jewels from the hour hand, and he finds out they're—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.73,0:09:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're the only ones who know that I sold off the diamonds and switched them for fakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.55,0:09:55.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, now that everyone knows Kaitō Kid's after it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.47,0:09:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,its price has jumped high, so it's the best time to sell it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.80,0:10:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whether they find out after the clock tower's moved or not is none of my concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.95,0:10:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, it would never be stolen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.29,0:10:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, great and elusive thief he may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.32,0:10:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but how could he ever steal that enormous clock tower in front of all these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.29,0:10:17.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stay out, Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.19,0:10:19.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give it to him, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.43,0:10:21.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey, Aoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.15,0:10:23.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the only one rooting against him here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.52,0:10:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.71,0:10:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, Keiko, have you seen Kaito?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.48,0:10:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.48,0:10:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said something about watching a magic show on TV tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.56,0:10:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.14,0:10:39.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I guess I'm the only one who remembers something that happened that long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.73,0:10:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.95,0:10:44.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw somebody who looked like Kid while on patrol?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.63,0:10:45.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.29,0:10:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He dropped this suspicious-looking hat and left!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.59,0:10:51.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is Kid's silk hat and cape!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.88,0:10:53.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you wait here a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.23,0:10:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.01,0:10:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Nakamori, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.76,0:10:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the silk hat and cape are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.01,0:11:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.01,0:11:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.04,0:11:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay! I've got approval from the Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.95,0:11:08.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please go explain the circumstances at the time and the man's features
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.32,0:11:11.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that you saw directly to the Inspector at the top floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.77,0:11:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.84,0:11:20.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That was easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.60,0:11:24.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Without Hakuba around, this is so easy that it ain't even fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.14,0:11:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here they come, Mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.16,0:11:32.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, there's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.96,0:11:33.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.73,0:11:38.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He puts out a strong and pure vibe, just like Kuroba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.96,0:11:44.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He has the cunning of the devil, and keen eyes that can see people's hearts for what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.74,0:11:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.41,0:11:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.89,0:11:57.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's an extra helicopter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.29,0:11:58.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's another support helicopter sent over by the Police HQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.29,0:12:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Support from HQ?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.98,0:12:03.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't remember asking for anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.56,0:12:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Kid's silk hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.95,0:12:07.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was told you'd come.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.88,0:12:10.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But please show me your police notebook and license, just to be sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.82,0:12:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.90,0:12:17.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please give me your name, age, and date of birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.11,0:12:20.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yōichi Sensui, 27 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.74,0:12:22.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Born June 2nd.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.61,0:12:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.71,0:12:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Nakamori's waiting for you on the top floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.56,0:12:28.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.53,0:12:33.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, just in case, give me your driver's license number.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.27,0:12:35.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.49,0:12:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's 628605-524810, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.17,0:12:49.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's Kaitō Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.66,0:12:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.72,0:12:53.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.99,0:12:55.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.18,0:12:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found Kid in the building?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.77,0:13:01.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir! Groups C and D are in pursuit!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.14,0:13:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you sure he's the real deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.84,0:13:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's certain. After he answered his name, age and birth date,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.65,0:13:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remembered to ask him for his driver's license number, and voila!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.16,0:13:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His driver's license number?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.73,0:13:17.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.45,0:13:28.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boy HQ sent said a disguise expert would probably memorize things normal people wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.73,0:13:30.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.54,0:13:33.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I repeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.67,0:13:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please seal off all entrances and exit the clock tower immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.93,0:13:39.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't open them until I give the word!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.58,0:13:44.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's just a bird in a cage with his wings clipped now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.19,0:13:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is group D, Nakamura and Kawada. We've lost sight of the target near the 3rd floor toilet!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.84,0:13:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please calm down. I'm sure he's still near you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.89,0:14:03.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has the air vent in one of those toilets been unscrewed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.88,0:14:06.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.64,0:14:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it has!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.00,0:14:10.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's where you'll find him then!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.52,0:14:12.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep up the pursuit!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.94,0:14:16.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.42,0:14:17.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hey, hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.16,0:14:21.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Inspector's really on the ball today!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.29,0:14:23.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Or is somebody helping him out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.18,0:14:26.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But who could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.15,0:14:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.59,0:14:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.11,0:14:33.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing, bringing a brat in here like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.89,0:14:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the commanding officer here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.99,0:14:39.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not even part of this division!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.49,0:14:42.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.20,0:14:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I promised him I'd let him board this helicopter once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.59,0:14:48.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I figured I might as well bring him along—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.97,0:14:50.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.14,0:14:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hate to be rude, but we don't have time to argue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.87,0:14:57.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to catch that thief, please do as I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.09,0:14:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.72,0:15:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been exposed before pulling off his heist. He'll be unsettled,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.50,0:15:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since his plan is falling apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.14,0:15:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the best chance to make the arrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.10,0:15:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.52,0:15:13.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who the hell are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.28,0:15:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.20,0:15:20.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Shin'ichi Kudo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.29,0:15:25.33,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi Kudō (17)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.19,0:15:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.75,0:15:34.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi Kudo?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.70,0:15:36.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I've heard of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.68,0:15:42.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a high school detective who's been solving baffling murder cases, one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.18,0:15:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this isn't your division either!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.48,0:15:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're after a phantom thief here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.96,0:15:49.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.84,0:15:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a high school student, he doesn't {\i1}have{\i0} a divi—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.23,0:15:55.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, this is a job for the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.87,0:15:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An outsider like you should just stay put in that helicopter of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.87,0:16:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Nakamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.01,0:16:03.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nakamura from Group D, after receiving word from the boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.59,0:16:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,discovered Kid disguised as a police officer inside an air vent!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.30,0:16:07.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're still in pursuit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.73,0:16:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.78,0:16:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Nakamura from Group D! It seems the target's trying to exit the ventilation duct!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.84,0:16:14.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.78,0:16:16.09,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.09,0:16:19.26,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Your target's already in your grasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.26,0:16:21.35,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Please tell me your present location.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.35,0:16:22.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.87,0:16:25.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been moving along in the dark, so I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.98,0:16:30.10,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I know I went up one flight of stairs from the 3rd floor, so this is the 4th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.10,0:16:31.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.14,0:16:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The exits from all 28 ventilation ducts within the building have already been secured.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.70,0:16:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please keep pursuing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.39,0:16:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He has no escape route.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.38,0:16:43.77,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The officers who are blocking the ventilation ducts' exits on the 4th floor should get ready to arrest him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.43,0:16:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How dare you order my men around...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.22,0:16:50.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Nakamura of Group D.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.19,0:16:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I lost sight of him near the ventilation duct's exit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.90,0:16:54.49,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's your present location?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.49,0:16:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.61,0:16:57.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The corridor to the east on the 4th floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.20,0:17:04.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The target abandoned his officer disguise and is fleeing down the stairs! Requesting backup!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.71,0:17:06.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,K-Kaitō Ki—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.30,0:17:10.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.15,0:17:15.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right! He panicked and ditched his officer disguise!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.50,0:17:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officers on the third and fourth floors, don't let him get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.38,0:17:26.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how does that boy in the helicopter have so much information about the clock tower's structure?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.27,0:17:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because I sent him the data!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.67,0:17:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.74,0:17:36.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By discarding that disguise in an area full of officers,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.48,0:17:45.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he's like a hermit crab disposing of its shell, crawling defenseless across the sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.35,0:17:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It makes no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.04,0:18:17.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's time, Inspector Nakamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.17,0:18:18.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.06,0:18:31.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.27,0:18:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Smoke came out of the scaffolding!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.94,0:18:34.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.28,0:19:02.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Nakamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.44,0:19:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clock's hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.35,0:19:05.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.18,0:19:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! They're gone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.60,0:19:19.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing! Kid is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.86,0:19:20.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.72,0:19:23.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kid, you jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.63,0:19:32.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.04,0:19:34.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's swaying?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.25,0:19:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the helicopter's swaying?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.88,0:19:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.09,0:19:39.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.76,0:19:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you going, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.64,0:19:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going up to check the clock's engine room!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.97,0:19:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but could you please bring the helicopter closer to the clock tower?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.97,0:19:54.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it, what's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.74,0:19:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anything new?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.16,0:20:00.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.38,0:20:02.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.01,0:20:05.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.96,0:20:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A police officer appeared from the ventilation duct and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.16,0:20:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.29,0:20:17.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sprayed something weird at us and went out that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.04,0:20:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.57,0:20:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had, he'd be clearly visible from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.50,0:20:26.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaitō Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.07,0:20:30.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.79,0:20:36.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's me, Nakamori! I found Kid! He's—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.54,0:20:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Nakamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.23,0:20:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologize for not having the time to play with you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.26,0:20:48.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.65,0:20:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would seem you have a Joker in your hand this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.37,0:20:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In my hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.84,0:21:00.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you must call someone here, do so after cracking
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.78,0:21:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the code carved into the center of the clock's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.42,0:21:04.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Code?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.79,0:21:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.86,0:21:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd appreciate it if you deciphered it before calling anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.56,0:21:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clock's face is swaying?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.48,0:21:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does this mean, Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.49,0:21:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's lighting up the clock's face along with the smokescreen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.29,0:21:26.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After turning off the light, the clock's face was covered with a giant screen that'd been set up beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.26,0:21:29.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a film of the clock without its hands was projected onto the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.36,0:21:33.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The film is being projected from a projector that's been assembled onto a foothold at the scaffolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.55,0:21:37.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that trick's pretty easy to figure out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.56,0:21:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. That trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.78,0:21:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...is just a ruse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.92,0:21:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's probably behind the screen right now removing the diamonds embedded onto the hour hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.51,0:21:51.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me borrow this for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.83,0:22:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey? Who fired?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.09,0:22:08.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.34,0:22:12.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}With the helicopter this close, my hang-glider won't get me anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.63,0:22:15.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now what?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.34,0:22:17.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now what do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.30,0:22:19.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.35,0:22:20.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.47,0:22:22.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I won't hit anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.14,0:22:25.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not the problem, Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.06,0:22:34.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now for the finale of this magic show. It's time to meet the man behind the curtain!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.14,0:23:02.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's something all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.89,0:23:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He fell onto the crowd along with the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.83,0:23:08.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Finding him in that crowd's pretty much impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.19,0:23:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megure here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.43,0:23:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.03,0:23:17.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you just shoot at me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.03,0:23:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.70,0:23:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Inspector, did he leave any message with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.04,0:23:29.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he said something about a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.54,0:23:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A code?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.09,0:23:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't make heads or tails of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.95,0:23:46.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was this really carved in the center of the clock's face?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.56,0:23:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.23,0:23:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, it's important evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.48,0:23:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll have to make them postpone moving the clock tower until the code's deciphered.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.48,0:23:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't need you to tell me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.42,0:24:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All's well that ends well, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.78,0:24:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clock tower's safe, and his heist ended in failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.37,0:24:10.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I wouldn't go that far, Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.46,0:24:13.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He left a code in the clock's face and left the clock tower for the police to take care of,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.92,0:24:19.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}stealing away the owner's plans to relocate it .
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.05,0:24:22.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It says so in the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.68,0:24:28.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If you change the katakana to romaji, and move the vowels one space each clockwise, you get...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.31,0:24:32.44,Signs,,0,0,0,,kono kane no ne wa watasenai
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.31,0:24:32.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"This bell shall not toll for you".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.87,0:24:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Inspector Megure, I never did find out the thief's name... {lol continuity patch}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.35,0:24:41.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh well, who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.37,0:24:53.33,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Are you waiting for someone too?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.33,0:24:55.83,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm supposed to meet up with my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.92,0:25:00.76,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But he said he might be busy with work, so we might not be able to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.13,0:25:03.55,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.43,0:25:07.56,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm Kaito Kuroba. Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.48,0:25:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Kaito Kuroba. Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.61,0:25:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaito!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.03,0:25:28.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would I ever forget that, you dope?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.87,0:25:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.33,0:25:36.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All your worrying got me reminiscing, Jii{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.04,0:25:38.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That clock tower job was full of close calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.82,0:25:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did become of that clock tower?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.88,0:25:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. You didn't know since you moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.93,0:25:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they {\i1}did{\i0} move it after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.31,0:25:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.77,0:25:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.35,0:25:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.11,0:26:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This bell...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.19,0:26:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police investigated afterwards and found out that the diamonds were fake,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.32,0:26:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the city bought the clock on the cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.54,0:26:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, time to get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.16,0:26:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The objective is a Big Jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.57,0:26:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A jewel in the possession of the Suzuki Financial Group, the Black Star!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.03,0:26:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master, I know it's too late to stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.03,0:26:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But as Tōichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} always said...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.30,0:26:30.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you face the audience, you step onto a battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.14,0:26:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must never be overconfident or underestimate them,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.97,0:26:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but see through their hearts and minds instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.68,0:26:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pay full attention to your hands to utilize all your skills, but maintain your smile and elegance all the while...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.19,0:26:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And no matter what happens, never forget your poker face, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.11,0:26:49.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.35,0:27:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.36,0:27:22.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.19,0:27:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, what's this? It gives me the creeps.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.95,0:27:32.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.03,0:27:32.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.87,0:27:34.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.20,0:27:39.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says "Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}" in calligraphic white letters on a black envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.04,0:27:44.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't have a stamp or the name of the sender.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.75,0:27:47.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probably just some kind of "join us" advertising thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.17,0:27:48.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.09,0:27:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.76,0:27:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"In honor of your wisdom, we would like to invite you to a formal gathering."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.39,0:28:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, just as I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.98,0:28:06.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet they're just trying to add some class to their party by inviting a Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.61,0:28:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.82,0:28:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.11,0:28:14.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It fell out of the envelope. It says "2 million yen", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.02,0:28:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,2... million yen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.75,0:28:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be weird to send something like this just for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.42,0:28:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they don't even know if you're coming or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.09,0:28:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.97,0:28:32.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't the name of the sender somewhere inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.51,0:28:36.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.47,0:28:40.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The Phantom of the Child Forsaken by God"?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.98,0:28:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that about?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.75,0:28:47.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Phantom of the Child Forsaken by God...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.46,0:29:10.30,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A strong heart's deductive power gets to the true essence of everything with an intense rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.30,0:29:12.17,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The curtains of the 21st Century open for Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.17,0:29:14.09,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Six detectives follow Kid's trail!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.09,0:29:15.76,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.76,0:29:17.51,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.51,0:29:19.43,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.86,0:30:57.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan, can you check the tire over on that side?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.15,0:30:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.16,0:31:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tire on this side is completely flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.62,0:31:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's flat?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.37,0:31:06.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a bummer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.17,0:31:17.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no spare, either, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.30,0:31:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.68,0:31:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.70,0:31:22.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.22,0:31:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a petrol station over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.27,0:31:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Talk about lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.89,0:31:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a Buddha in Hell indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.68,0:32:05.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it. Shortcut, my eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.37,0:32:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did I listen to that old man at the petrol station?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.85,0:32:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.31,0:32:13.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this really the right way?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.88,0:32:15.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.31,0:32:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took me into his stand and sold me this really expensive map 'cause he said it had this area in detail!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.99,0:32:25.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this ain't the right road, that geezer's gonna pay for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.79,0:32:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like we're back on a real road!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.34,0:32:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, it {\i1}was{\i0} a shortcut!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.30,0:32:42.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that it, on the right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.46,0:32:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Sunset Manor we're heading for.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.76,0:32:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a pretty eerie looking building.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.36,0:32:53.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks more like Castle Dracula than Sunset Manor.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.69,0:32:58.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, are we really going in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.23,0:32:59.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.65,0:33:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They sent me an invitation to a banquet "in honor of my wisdom"
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.95,0:33:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a check for two million yen. How could I refuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.27,0:33:10.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't the invitation signed with some creepy phrase?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.75,0:33:15.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that child forsaken by God thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.04,0:33:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.59,0:33:18.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just somebody bluffing nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.67,0:33:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.76,0:33:29.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, maybe we shouldn't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.06,0:33:30.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've already come this far!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.68,0:33:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what if Dracula shows up for real?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.55,0:33:36.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.11,0:33:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no such thing as Dracula in Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.15,0:33:41.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there was anything, it'd be uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.32,0:33:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mountain witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.37,0:33:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A mountain witch!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.21,0:34:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's some way to greet a woman on a first meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.67,0:34:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.35,0:34:07.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Granny, what are you doing out in a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.05,0:34:08.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.85,0:34:12.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sweet little Fiat has broken down.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.99,0:34:15.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for someone to pass by.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.40,0:34:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're going to the Sunset Manor too, aren't you?\NIf it's not too much trouble, would you give me a lift?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.57,0:34:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.36,0:34:28.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can sit in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.28,0:34:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And while we're at it, would you please move my things from my Fiat into your car?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.91,0:34:35.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.33,0:34:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry for the bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.18,0:34:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad, are we still going to take long?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.60,0:34:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's still gonna take a bit to get there, but why? Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.60,0:34:59.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to use the toilet!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.56,0:35:00.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.61,0:35:03.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young lady, I don't mean to intrude.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.94,0:35:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the headmaster of my primary school always used to say
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.03,0:35:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that success comes to those who seize the day,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.08,0:35:20.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,while those who let a golden opportunity pass by will never get a second chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.92,0:35:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why didn't you go to the lavatory back at the petrol station?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.72,0:35:29.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd you know that, granny?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.84,0:35:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That we'd stopped at the petrol station, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.26,0:35:36.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's pretty easy, little one.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.02,0:35:41.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the empty ashtray and the still-new cigarette butts on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.44,0:35:46.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ashtray was so stuffed that cigarette butts were falling out,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.36,0:35:48.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the gentleman must be a heavy smoker.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.07,0:35:50.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now it's empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.59,0:35:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only place you could've cleaned it out recently was that petrol station you passed 10 km ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.11,0:36:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man kind enough to give a strange old lady a lift
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.12,0:36:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,would never throw his cigarettes out of the window of his car in front of his daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.96,0:36:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you, granny?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.33,0:36:10.22,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm Furuyo Senma.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.22,0:36:13.22,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Furuyo Senma (63)\NDetective
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.22,0:36:13.60,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A detective just like you, Mr. Sleeping Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.60,0:36:15.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furuyo Senma?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.93,0:36:22.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That famous detective who can solve a cases just by sitting down in an armchair?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.10,0:36:26.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, flattering an old lady will get you nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.32,0:36:28.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.90,0:36:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll hang on to this ashtray of yours for the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.20,0:36:34.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.16,0:36:38.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't smoke in front of me, even after we reach the manor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.03,0:36:42.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I despise cigarette smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.96,0:36:44.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.51,0:36:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's Sunset Manor up ahead. Step on the gas!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.60,0:37:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.84,0:37:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, open the back, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.39,0:37:46.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa. Up close, it looks even more like a haunted house.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.73,0:37:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, I'm going inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.40,0:37:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.86,0:37:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toilet, toilet...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.61,0:37:58.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa, check out these fancy cars!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.99,0:38:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.54,0:38:03.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Benz, a Ferrari and a Porsche.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.23,0:38:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's certainly full of dangerous cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.54,0:38:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that an Alfa Romeo?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.17,0:38:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's classy!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.30,0:38:13.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.51,0:38:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hands off my girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.43,0:38:23.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It took me five years to tame that shrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.89,0:38:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want her to get upset by another man touching her.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.90,0:38:30.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it, whiskers?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.78,0:38:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Whiskers?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.19,0:38:34.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Long time no see, Mogi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.40,0:38:36.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you were invited too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.38,0:38:39.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Granny Senma!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.41,0:38:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that mean you were invited too?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.90,0:38:42.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Mogi?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.29,0:38:46.75,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Harufumi Mogi (39)\NDetective
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.91,0:38:45.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}He's Detective Harufumi Mogi!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.25,0:38:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.38,0:38:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I read in the papers that you'd been shot by the mafia in Chicago last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.13,0:38:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's old news. I don't think about the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.22,0:39:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not still a bachelor, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.85,0:39:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're turning 40 in just three days...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.14,0:39:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think about the future either.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.60,0:39:12.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All I need now is a little grub to silence my moaning gut.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.91,0:39:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.58,0:39:27.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mogi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} and Senma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.29,0:39:28.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've been waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.96,0:39:30.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.01,0:39:38.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This looks like...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.18,0:39:39.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...a haunted house, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.18,0:39:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please put your umbrellas here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.85,0:39:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.22,0:39:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.31,0:39:47.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.31,0:39:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.23,0:39:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just went to the kitchen, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.61,0:39:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall correctly, he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.11,0:39:57.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The gourmet detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.34,0:39:59.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Shukuzen Ōgami.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.86,0:40:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.91,0:40:03.87,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shukuzen Ōgami (51)\NDetective
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.28,0:40:03.87,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The cook's fallen ill and can't come in today?!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.87,0:40:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't what I was promised!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.95,0:40:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've come all this way to enjoy a banquet!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.50,0:40:13.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry, sir. The ingredients are ready, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.13,0:40:17.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then lead me to the kitchen! I'll make the meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.17,0:40:22.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gastronomy and murder are the only disciplines that can occupy my prodigious mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.85,0:40:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.73,0:40:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry to have kept you waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.56,0:40:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this? Calling four detectives to an old house in the mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.57,0:40:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.36,0:40:43.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We actually invited {\i1}six{\i0} detectives altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.18,0:40:45.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C'mon now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.95,0:40:48.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're telling me there are two more?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.25,0:40:50.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, a woman and a teenage boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.54,0:40:53.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A teenage boy? Could it be Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.09,0:40:55.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.54,0:40:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probably Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.80,0:41:05.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. Those two were on the invitation list I received from my master,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.68,0:41:07.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I couldn't get in touch with Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.14,0:41:11.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s mother told me he wouldn't be attending
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.65,0:41:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because he has to study for his midterms.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.40,0:41:22.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since those two couldn't come, the master allowed Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} to bring two members of his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.95,0:41:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So where is this crazy detective lover anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.29,0:41:31.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I haven't met him in person yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.83,0:41:34.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you got the list from him, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.67,0:41:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, when I interviewed for my position as his maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.34,0:41:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was a very strange interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.51,0:41:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.38,0:41:48.39,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Aki Ishihara (23)\NMaid
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.67,0:41:45.97,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.97,0:41:50.18,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The job paid very well, so there were many applicants.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.18,0:41:53.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when I entered the interview room,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.35,0:42:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,all I found were a PC, a letter instructing me about the banquet, and a list of people to invite.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.57,0:42:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was nobody in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.15,0:42:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I was left with no choice but to read the papers as instructed on the PC.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.41,0:42:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then suddenly I heard a noise, and the words "you're hired" showed up on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.21,0:42:20.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you don't even know why you were hired?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.34,0:42:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.88,0:42:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you've talked to him since then, right? You just said you got your master's approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.76,0:42:32.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, all our conversations have been through e-mail on my mobile phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.31,0:42:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This sounds really interesting. The thrill's killing me!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.78,0:42:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was already electrified the moment I saw that funny pattern on that door.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.53,0:42:49.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does look pretty strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.03,0:42:51.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what it's a pattern of.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.99,0:42:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be careful, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.50,0:42:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'm not mistaken, that's probably the remains of an old bloodstain.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.17,0:42:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.34,0:43:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're joking, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.21,0:43:03.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, they're real.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.30,0:43:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Specifically, a blood spatter that struck the door at an entry angle of roughly 45°.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.06,0:43:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not just the door, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.77,0:43:15.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are old bloodstains on the wall, streaming downward.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.52,0:43:17.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there are blood droplets on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.14,0:43:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And although they were wiped away,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.06,0:43:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there are bloodstains here and there throughout the whole mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.74,0:43:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like these bloodstains don't belong to just one or two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.16,0:43:32.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are indeed impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.12,0:43:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Luminol.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.08,0:43:44.34,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Spray it onto blood, and active oxygen inside the blood will oxidize it,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.34,0:43:47.34,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,giving off a bluish-purple fluorescent light.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.55,0:43:49.09,Signs,,0,0,0,,3-aminophtalhydrazide
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.63,0:43:53.10,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You make good deductions, former coroner Ikumi Sōda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.30,0:43:57.31,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ikumi Sōda (29)\NDetective
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.06,0:43:58.94,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm flattered to hear that, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.98,0:44:03.69,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Saguru Hakuba (17)\NDetective
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.40,0:44:02.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm Saguru Hakuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.69,0:44:03.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.57,0:44:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hakuba?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.98,0:44:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean you're Police Superintendent Hakuba's—
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.07,0:44:14.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quite so. Police Superintendent Hakuba is indeed my father, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.37,0:44:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A falcon?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.50,0:44:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I do apologize for startling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.63,0:44:31.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the time we've spent together in England, Watson here seems to have picked up a fancy for blood.{I heard Watson is a she, but might be fanon, so going with "it" to be safe/Viz goes with "he" -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.97,0:44:34.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Watson"?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.72,0:44:37.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm truly glad I came back home, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.02,0:44:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After forty years, I am finally able to step inside the scene of the tragedy
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.69,0:44:46.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that I had heard of only in frightened whispers.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.53,0:44:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's more than enough to arouse my intellectual interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.86,0:44:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tragedy?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.13,0:45:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.17,0:45:11.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.93,0:45:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, thank you, good sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.72,0:45:21.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about this, Mr. Sleeping Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.23,0:45:24.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.31,0:45:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, look, I've got a straight!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.90,0:45:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I win again!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.15,0:45:32.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She sure is as strong as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.07,0:45:33.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.07,0:45:38.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No cheating now, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.54,0:45:40.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, that Jack on your left.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.37,0:45:42.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's another card stuck to it, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.71,0:45:45.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.17,0:45:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, I didn't notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.29,0:45:51.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think they were stuck together this whole time...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.14,0:45:58.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.95,0:46:00.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's blood on the playing card!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.10,0:46:05.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, my, my! Blood has splattered there too, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.73,0:46:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, the maid was saying
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.85,0:46:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that the things here are just as they were at the time of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.23,0:46:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That practically nothing has been moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.40,0:46:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then whatever happened happened in this room too?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.37,0:46:20.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you all for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.12,0:46:25.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The banquet is ready. My master awaits you in the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.20,0:46:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the big boss finally makes his appearance...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.33,0:46:29.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.72,0:46:38.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I lost my appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.18,0:46:44.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.61,0:46:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please go on inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.16,0:46:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.99,0:47:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with the costume?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.99,0:47:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think you've been watching too much TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.87,0:47:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Six of the world's most magnificent detectives!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.12,0:47:11.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the Sunset Manor!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.00,0:47:16.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.93,0:47:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bring out the dishes in the order I instructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.95,0:47:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.60,0:47:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've invited all of you here to see if you can figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.49,0:47:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,where in this house I have hidden my treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.61,0:47:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the entire enormous fortune I've gathered over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.74,0:47:45.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and your lives are at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.91,0:47:47.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Our lives?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.38,0:47:53.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that sound?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.29,0:47:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be alarmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.88,0:47:57.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've just rid you of your means of escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.45,0:47:58.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.49,0:48:01.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm always getting chased around by the likes of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.60,0:48:07.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I thought I'd chase you for a change.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.77,0:48:11.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also destroyed the only bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.77,0:48:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so even if your cars weren't scrap, you'd have no way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.28,0:48:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I'm sure you can guess, this house has no phone line, and we're well out of mobile range.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.16,0:48:24.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you can't get any outside help.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.12,0:48:25.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.91,0:48:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a game. I will give half of my treasure to the detective who finds it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.58,0:48:36.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and I'll also show the winner how to leave this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.13,0:48:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.01,0:48:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I say baloney. I don't cozy up to cowards who sneak around in masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.31,0:48:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come now, you can't play on an empty stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.31,0:48:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please enjoy the dinner to your heart's content—your last supper.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.73,0:48:57.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a dummy with a speaker in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.65,0:48:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That dirty...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.24,0:48:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.57,0:49:02.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who could be behind all this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.61,0:49:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.11,0:49:06.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't believe a man like you, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, would come here not knowing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.62,0:49:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was written on the invitation, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.75,0:49:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The Phantom of the Child Forsaken by God."
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.42,0:49:21.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A phantom, somebody who appears out of thin air like a ghost...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.26,0:49:25.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The word "child" in the sentence was written with the character亻attached to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.30,0:49:28.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it refers to the child of a beast, as this character is used to write words like "pony"{ko'uma, on the right} and "puppy".
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.89,0:49:31.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The animal forsaken by God is the goat,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.93,0:49:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the animal separated from the sheep in the New Testament.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.65,0:49:38.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The line is referring to a baby goat.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.21,0:49:44.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in English, a baby goat is called...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.32,0:49:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A "kid"...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.74,0:49:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.53,0:49:51.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it'll be clearer if I put it this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.25,0:49:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.67,0:49:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.29,0:49:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.00,0:50:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That young thief who spirits valuables away like magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.63,0:50:10.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mastermind who baffles the police with as many faces and voices as the stars in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.68,0:50:15.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The main dish that all detectives are dying to spear on the end of a fork.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.35,0:50:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A villain putting on airs that I can't wait to throw in the clink.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.99,0:50:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the only person who ever got the best of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.36,0:50:28.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the crowds see his white cape fluttering in the night, they all shout...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.49,0:50:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaitō Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.38,0:50:41.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kaitō Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.38,0:50:45.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sure is an honest guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.30,0:50:48.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The moment his name came up, he gave us a hint about his identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.89,0:50:52.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's that cool style of his.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.93,0:50:57.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's here in this mansion... I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.02,0:51:00.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I don't know what you're up to...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.40,0:51:06.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But can you fool us all? You're up against seven master sleuths...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.86,0:51:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that Kaitō Kid invited us to this banquet?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.79,0:51:17.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that he gathered the six of us here to compete intellectually,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.75,0:51:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as have a reputation of being good detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.71,0:51:26.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At stake are all the treasures he's stolen, and our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.92,0:51:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's probably somewhere watching us right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.55,0:51:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I noticed this house was swarming with hidden cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.94,0:51:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have brought the {\i1}hors d'œuvres{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.20,0:51:52.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, our so-called last supper.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.29,0:51:59.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, maid?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.96,0:52:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.08,0:52:07.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By any chance did the master tell you to place the food on the table in a certain order?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.63,0:52:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.30,0:52:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was told to work clockwise from Hakuba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.26,0:52:19.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He called this the "last supper", but the game has only just begun. Funny, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.60,0:52:25.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come, now. You can't suspect poison. I cooked this myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.78,0:52:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\q2}But the forks, knives, spoons, wine glasses and\Nteacups were all here on the table before we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.16,0:52:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And our host chose the seating arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.54,0:52:38.66,Signs,,0,0,0,,Saguru Hakuba
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.71,0:52:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cold-blooded murder isn't his style, but he may have a highly unamusing joke planned for one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.55,0:52:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I advise all of you to wipe your cups and cutlery with a handkerchief before you eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.30,0:52:59.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I don't like the way this stooge is running the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.52,0:53:03.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to do a game of rock, paper, scissors and change seats then?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.86,0:53:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But what if someone ill-fatedly gets the poisoned seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.15,0:53:12.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's that, take it as fate, and cry in the coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.49,0:53:14.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.12,0:53:22.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.37,0:53:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as expected of the Gourmet Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.35,0:53:26.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You truly are an amazing cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.67,0:53:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went through a lot of training to satisfy this tongue of mine, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.22,0:53:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps I was too suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.68,0:53:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.93,0:53:38.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't let our guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.68,0:53:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, people, how do you like the last supper that I prepared for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.02,0:53:45.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess who's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.69,0:53:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's time to tell you why I chose this place for our game. It didn't come cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.41,0:54:01.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, take a look at the plates in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.87,0:54:04.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.12,0:54:08.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They've all got this creepy logo of a bird with a large beak.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.34,0:54:11.76,Signs,,0,0,0,,karasu
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.34,0:54:11.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this a crow?{karasu}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.76,0:54:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could this be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.05,0:54:15.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you figured it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.18,0:54:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the millionaire who died a mysterious death a half a century ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.06,0:54:25.02,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ren'ya Karasuma
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.77,0:54:25.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the crest of Ren'ya Karasuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.73,0:54:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Ren'ya Karasuma?!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.19,0:54:33.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not just the flatware. Everything from the doors, flooring and handrails,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.82,0:54:36.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,down to the chess pieces and the playing cards in the living room,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.57,0:54:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was specially ordered by Karasuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.87,0:54:44.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This manor is Karasuma's vacation home.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.87,0:54:53.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or rather, it {\i1}was{\i0} a vacation home, until one stormy night 40 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.34,0:54:55.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when this manor house was struck by a blood-chilling tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.93,0:55:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are all fine detectives, so I'm sure you've all noticed the numerous bloodstains.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.02,0:55:10.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.48,0:55:17.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It all happened one night 40 years ago, when this house was still beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.49,0:55:23.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Movers and shakers of the business world came here for a private gathering.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.83,0:55:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was called a memorial for Ren'ya Karasuma, who had just died at age 99.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.54,0:55:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in reality, it was an auction to sell off the priceless art
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.30,0:55:36.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that Karasuma had collected during his lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.09,0:55:42.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were over 300 pieces, and the auction was scheduled to continue for three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.56,0:55:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the second night, that stormy night...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.44,0:56:02.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two men were freezing, and with trembling lips, remarked that they had lost their way in the storm,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.32,0:56:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and they would like to spend the night until the storm subsided.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.37,0:56:10.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first the auction host was reluctant to let them in,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.42,0:56:15.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the man handed the host over a small parcel in exchange for letting them stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.05,0:56:19.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents of the parcel seemed to be something like a cigarette,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.97,0:56:22.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the host smoked it as the men instructed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.93,0:56:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soon he became much friendlier, and let the two men inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.98,0:56:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other guests who were watching were urged by the two to smoke likewise
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.90,0:56:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the smoke gradually filled the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.90,0:56:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me that the parcel was...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.99,0:56:42.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Marijuana...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.28,0:56:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The guests had a enjoyed a merry, boisterous time for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.91,0:56:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but after a while things began to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.96,0:56:55.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man screamed as if he had seen the devil,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.63,0:56:59.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,carried the item that he had bid for and now owned, and ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.47,0:57:05.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A woman started crying as if asking someone for forgiveness until her tears dried out.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.47,0:57:12.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet another man happily stabbed himself in the arm time and again with the pen that he was holding.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.94,0:57:16.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soon people began to fight for the works of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.52,0:57:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They used antique swords from the auction to kill each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.11,0:57:25.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The elite gathering turned into a vision of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.16,0:57:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the nightmare ended, the two men disappeared with the art,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.33,0:57:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,leaving eight dead and\Nover ten people in a coma.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.59,0:57:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why wasn't a case this big made public?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.39,0:57:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I imagine that gathering included people with powerful relatives and political connections.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.64,0:57:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.15,0:58:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't clear who killed whom.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.32,0:58:06.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must have thought it would be better to cover it up than to get the police involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.95,0:58:11.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet that was the crooks' plan from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.00,0:58:16.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that was certainly pleasant dinner conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.59,0:58:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you understand now why I chose this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.51,0:58:33.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want you detectives to reenact the tragedy that occurred here 40 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.02,0:58:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That ugly scene of people fighting over the treasure and killing each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.94,0:58:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What foolishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.57,0:58:47.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figure it's too cruel to make you all just search blindly all throughout this building,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.36,0:58:49.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so let me give you a hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.78,0:58:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hint?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.91,0:58:58.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the night the two travelers looked up at the sky, a demon appeared in the castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.29,0:59:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the king ran wild with his treasure in hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.05,0:59:06.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The queen wept for forgiveness, her tears falling into the Holy Grail,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.84,0:59:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the knight killed himself with his own sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.64,0:59:15.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.73,0:59:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It took some time for me to come up with a riddle that fit the tragedy of this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.36,0:59:24.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't you think it's perfect for the deadly game you're about to play?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.65,0:59:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.15,0:59:31.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't just order us to kill each other. We have to be willing to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.45,0:59:37.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cannot walk out of this game.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.50,0:59:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, you are all under the spell I have cast over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.17,0:59:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, the game will start when someone screams.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.06,0:59:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't forget...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.43,1:00:01.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who finds the treasure must enter the location of the treasure in the computer
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.06,1:00:04.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that is in the room on the fourth floor in the center tower.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.07,1:00:10.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I promise to give you half the treasure and tell you the way out of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.99,1:00:14.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mogi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.04,1:00:18.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mogi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.13,1:00:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,J-Just kidding!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.13,1:00:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a bad old man you are, really...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.67,1:00:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, sorry...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.13,1:00:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a token of my apology, I'm out.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.26,1:00:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got no interest in treasure hunts.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.39,1:00:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how do you intend to get out of here?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.10,1:00:39.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.39,1:00:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're not castaways on an island, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.52,1:00:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I have to, I'll hike all the way down the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.03,1:00:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you all later then, detectives!{Viz's "So long, fellow shamuses!" might be too obscure}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.63,1:01:07.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, old man, joke's only funny the first time!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.97,1:01:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,22:34 and 51 seconds. Cardio-respiratory arrest confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.80,1:01:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no chance of resuscitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.56,1:01:21.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.27,1:01:26.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His lips are pink. No sign of cyanosis.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.11,1:01:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His breath has the almond scent that indicates cyanide.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.20,1:01:34.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the tea the old man was drinking had potassium cyanide in it?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.87,1:01:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not getting any redox reaction...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.54,1:01:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it wasn't in the tea.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.79,1:01:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what on earth happened to him?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.29,1:01:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The die has been thrown!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.00,1:01:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please do your best to find the treasure
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.17,1:01:53.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,for the sake of Detective Ōgami, who gave his life
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.84,1:01:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to start this game with a bang...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.93,1:01:56.80,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Cut the bull!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.93,1:02:00.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you are still alive...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.73,1:02:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cassette tape...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.56,1:02:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like it was connected to a timer.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.06,1:02:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A timer?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.82,1:02:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you given an exact time to bring the food out?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.40,1:02:17.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he had specific times for everything. The {\i1}hors d'œuvres{\i0}, soup, main dish, dessert...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.87,1:02:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the killer wasn't spying on us and talking through a microphone.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.54,1:02:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was just playing a pre-recorded tape.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.42,1:02:29.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now we know two things.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.80,1:02:38.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One, the killer intended to kill Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from the start, and two, the killer could be among us.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.65,1:02:48.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think the killer's one of us?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.40,1:02:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take that tape for instance.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.48,1:02:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Any of us could've set the tape recorder up beforehand
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.28,1:02:58.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and pretended to listen as we all ate dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.16,1:03:01.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.83,1:03:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And sit in this same dining room as Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, without us noticing...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.75,1:03:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was made to drink the cyanide and poisoned himself to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.84,1:03:15.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right in front of our very eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.18,1:03:19.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the tape,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.30,1:03:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer knew exactly when the victim was going to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.43,1:03:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The problem is that there's no sign of any cyanide compounds in the tea
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.85,1:03:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that he was drinking until just before he died.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.57,1:03:37.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The poison could have been on the rim of the cup and not in the tea itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.20,1:03:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think so. I saw him take several sips before he died.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.33,1:03:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the killer you're all talking about is Kaitō Kid, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.37,1:03:53.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought he never killed people...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.30,1:03:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. As far as I know, this is the first case.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.55,1:04:00.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we ain't gonna get far just flapping our jaws.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.34,1:04:02.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't we take a stroll outside
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.35,1:04:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and see if our cars have really been blown up?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.64,1:04:06.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.60,1:04:12.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There may be a car that escaped the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.40,1:04:18.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or the explosion could have been a hoax.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.09,1:04:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My rental car...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.88,1:04:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My Ferrari seems to be well-done too.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.47,1:04:43.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My Alfa and Ōgami's Porsche are history!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.47,1:04:46.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that Benz yours, then?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.43,1:04:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.60,1:04:50.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had my nanny drive me here.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.31,1:04:52.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.77,1:04:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came here in Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s car.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.61,1:04:58.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So whose Benz is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.44,1:05:02.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's the master's car.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.32,1:05:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was already parked here when I came in this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.29,1:05:12.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then somebody else is in this house?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.63,1:05:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think he blew up my car in the back?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.59,1:05:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The back? You mean you have a car here?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.01,1:05:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.97,1:05:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master told me to park my car in the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.81,1:05:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any shortcut to the back gate?!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.89,1:05:33.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Through the enclosed garden...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.99,1:05:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go to the back gate by going to the left from the kitchen!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.70,1:05:48.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, your car's just fine!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.16,1:05:52.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think this is fishy?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.00,1:05:56.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That rat probably just forgot to set a bomb in this one!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.38,1:06:00.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, why don't I drive out to see if the bridge is standing?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.01,1:06:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.26,1:06:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I will too.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.51,1:06:04.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.39,1:06:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now, too many captains will sink the ship.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.39,1:06:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.81,1:06:14.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't want to end up on a phantom ship while we're looking for the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.39,1:06:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's toss a coin to see who goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.86,1:06:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got some change with me right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.53,1:06:29.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, you're pretty well prepared, little one!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.33,1:06:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a rather primitive method.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.83,1:06:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess we've got no choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.46,1:06:38.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoever gets heads...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.67,1:06:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...will take the car out to the bridge and check it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.85,1:06:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's me, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Mogi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.03,1:07:07.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please be careful, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.94,1:07:19.40,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}T-That's...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.29,1:07:21.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.72,1:07:23.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.80,1:07:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come, let's go back inside!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.80,1:07:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.47,1:07:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.85,1:07:37.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.15,1:07:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bridge is completely wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.11,1:07:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, granny Senma!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.44,1:07:47.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Turn the headlights up so we can see below!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.11,1:07:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.75,1:07:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Erm, headlights, headlights...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.08,1:07:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think the killer will strike again?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.58,1:07:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.37,1:08:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's still too early to end this game.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.18,1:08:15.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Senma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.81,1:08:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Senma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.37,1:08:38.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Senma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered?!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.24,1:08:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Looks like the jalopy was set to blow if you fiddled with the headlights.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.67,1:08:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.05,1:08:48.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we just sit around, we'll all get killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.59,1:08:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's search the house and see if we're really alone!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.43,1:08:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We girls will search together.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.14,1:09:00.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way we can go to the ladies' room as a group.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.02,1:09:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.69,1:09:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened to the pale kid with the bleached hair?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.90,1:09:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beats me.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.90,1:09:09.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he's feeding the falcon that he brought along with him?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.34,1:09:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get a load of that fancy-lookin' thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.05,1:09:35.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see fresh scratch marks on the edge of this piano.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.35,1:09:38.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably claw marks from the hawk.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.35,1:09:42.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess the kid's been doing a little solo investigation.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.73,1:09:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! There's something stuck between the keys!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.45,1:09:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this the secret code that indicates the location of the treasure that he was talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.41,1:10:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why is it mimeographed on rice paper?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.00,1:10:12.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody probably printed a whole lot of these when things like photocopiers didn't exist yet,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.47,1:10:15.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and for some reason, distributed it to many people.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.51,1:10:23.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, everything he told us about the tragedy from 40 years ago and the secret code
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.35,1:10:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,indicating the hidden treasure...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.07,1:10:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all a bunch of baloney.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.57,1:10:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{Arere?}Hey, the piano's wet.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.57,1:10:39.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.29,1:10:44.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that dame's luminol.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.46,1:10:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then she was here too.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.33,1:10:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, whiskers, douse the lights!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.34,1:10:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quick!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.11,1:11:17.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the maid?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.61,1:11:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she'd be waiting in the hall. Could you go take a look?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.29,1:11:23.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.21,1:11:27.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ms. Maid?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.17,1:11:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ms. Maid?!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.47,1:11:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Letters written in blood on the piano!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.85,1:11:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So something really did happen 40 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.44,1:11:50.44,Signs,,0,0,0,,I finally got my hands on the trump card that will decipher Karasuma's riddle.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.48,1:11:52.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A trump card...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.48,1:11:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...?!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.12,1:12:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it {\i1}was{\i0} you after all.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.63,1:12:18.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer wouldn't risk getting into a car with a bomb in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.38,1:12:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That leaves Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the maid, you and me—the ones who stayed behind.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.02,1:12:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Careful where you point that, young man.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.19,1:12:35.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it under my pillow in my room.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.11,1:12:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were planning to pin the crime on me, were you?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.03,1:12:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, what a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.53,1:12:45.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was thinking exactly the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.83,1:12:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I made the exact same deduction as you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.67,1:12:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A gunshot?!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.55,1:12:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It came from the central tower!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.39,1:13:09.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No good...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.73,1:13:11.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bullet's went right through his chest.{untimed kuso following}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.69,1:13:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.48,1:13:15.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stairs!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.32,1:13:17.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Somebody's using the stairs!{untimed kuso following}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.36,1:13:22.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.41,1:13:29.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A PC?{unsure about thoughts style}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.41,1:13:34.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This must be where we're supposed to come if we find the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.88,1:13:39.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sōta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.55,1:13:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.22,1:13:45.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Turn the knob from the inside and a needle pops out!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.93,1:13:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Any mook who came here to enter their answer
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.44,1:13:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,would get a poisoned needle in the palm when they tried to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.61,1:13:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But where on earth is the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.82,1:14:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cut the act!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.20,1:14:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way the dame would walk into a trap she set herself.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.45,1:14:13.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I found your daughter and the maid out cold in the hall.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.62,1:14:16.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm guessin' that gunshot was a red herring.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.60,1:14:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only people who could've done this were you and me...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.46,1:14:23.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and it ain't me.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.22,1:14:29.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That just leaves you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.90,1:14:42.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspects must be punished.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.24,1:14:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No hard feelings...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.78,1:14:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Sleepin' Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.30,1:15:03.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.15,1:15:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I suspected, not even the greatest detectives can solve this riddle.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.32,1:15:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My hidden camera! It shut off!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.86,1:15:28.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.07,1:15:31.95,Signs,,0,0,0,,I have the solution to the riddle.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.07,1:15:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody is inputting data?!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.37,1:15:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who on earth could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.87,1:15:36.37,Signs,,0,0,0,,I'd like to tell you in person. Come down to the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.37,1:15:40.96,Signs,,0,0,0,,I am the seventh detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.67,1:15:42.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.34,1:15:45.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I have the solution to the riddle.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.63,1:15:49.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'd like to tell you in person. Come down to the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.76,1:15:51.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I am the seventh detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.64,1:15:53.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This can't be...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.81,1:16:00.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the detectives I invited are dead!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.86,1:16:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is no seventh detective!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.15,1:16:06.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is it? Who could have...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.49,1:16:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't think that somebody who rigged a bomb go a car would {\i1}drive{\i0} it, barring suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.00,1:16:22.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I can think of a reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.00,1:16:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's if you wanted to make people {\i1}think{\i0} you died in the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.30,1:16:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.97,1:16:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Senma?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.86,1:16:46.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. You got out of the car and hid behind a bush just before the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.40,1:16:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you made your way back here and monitored us
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.41,1:16:55.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from a room somewhere, using the cameras hidden all over the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.70,1:16:59.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly, child. It's true that I escaped that explosion,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.71,1:17:04.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but only because I noticed the bomb at the last minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.34,1:17:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't we toss coins to decide who would ride in the car?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.68,1:17:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not really. You knew that you were going to take the car even before the coins were tossed.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.89,1:17:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You placed a coin with the head facing up on the back of your hand before you tossed the real coin.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.85,1:17:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You covered your left hand with your right one to hide it,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.31,1:17:28.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and pretended to catch the coin that you flicked.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.15,1:17:29.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you actually let the flicked coin drop onto the ground,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.49,1:17:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and showed the first coin that you'd put on the back of your hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.78,1:17:34.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how many times we tossed coins, you'd always get heads!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.78,1:17:40.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw you use a ¥10 coin to test Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s tea.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.66,1:17:45.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know a lot of coin tricks, don't you,\NMs. "Phantom of the Child Forsaken by God"?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.38,1:17:51.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you claiming I'm the host?\NThe criminal who killed Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.47,1:17:53.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.30,1:17:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did I make Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} alone take the cyanide in this dining room,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.18,1:18:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and just how was I able to predict the time?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.19,1:18:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was no poison in his tea.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.31,1:18:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was sitting in between Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and me...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.49,1:18:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, didn't we do rock, paper, scissors to decide where to sit?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.07,1:18:17.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't matter which seats we chose.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.41,1:18:23.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you put potassium cyanide on {\i1}everybody's{\i0} teacup beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.75,1:18:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You applied the poison at the spot where the handle meets the cup.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.42,1:18:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was exactly where Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s right thumb would touch the cup...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.26,1:18:37.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,including the thumbnail he bites when he's lost in thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.47,1:18:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During the recording, which you made using a voice modulator,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.48,1:18:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he bit his nail while listening to the riddle about the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.48,1:18:50.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By ordering the maid to bring out the tea just beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.48,1:18:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you were able to poison Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and {\i1}only{\i0} Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.49,1:18:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at the moment you knew he'd be thinking about your riddle.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.49,1:19:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I thought we all agreed to wipe off our cups and plates before using them.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.50,1:19:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.98,1:19:10.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's awfully careless for Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, a famed detective, to have forgotten that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.21,1:19:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if he was your partner in crime and helped you arrange this banquet,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.09,1:19:17.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there's nothing strange about him not wiping the cup,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.64,1:19:20.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since he never thought he'd be the one killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.31,1:19:28.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had my suspicions when I heard the Benz was already parked in front of the house
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.44,1:19:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when the maid arrived.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.69,1:19:33.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To leave the Mercedes at this isolated spot, you'd need at least two conspirators:
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.90,1:19:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,one to drive the Mercedes here, and one to drive up with a different car and pick the first person up.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.24,1:19:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, you waited by the side of the road and had us pick you up
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.33,1:19:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so you'd have the chance to tell Detective Mouri not to smoke.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.63,1:19:53.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would be the only one who died.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.71,1:19:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had put a cyanide-coated cigarette in his mouth after grabbing it with his fingertips,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.76,1:20:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he'd go straight to the afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.87,1:20:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You hired the maid because you watched her on a hidden camera during the interview
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.77,1:20:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and noticed that she had a habit of biting her nail too.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.98,1:20:12.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and you figured that you could kill her using the same method that you used to kill Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.32,1:20:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.10,1:20:19.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You killed Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, your accomplice, and made it look as if you'd been killed by someone else,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.16,1:20:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and tried to psychologically manipulate the other detectives.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.78,1:20:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once one of them solved the riddle and found the treasure, you planned to kill the survivors.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.84,1:20:34.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like Ren'ya Karasuma did forty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.97,1:20:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found the name "Kyōsuke Senma" at the end of the words written in blood on the piano.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.59,1:20:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.01,1:20:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's my father's name.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.35,1:20:51.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was an archaeologist. Forty years ago, he was invited to this house.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.88,1:20:54.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A multimillionaire who was over 100 years old
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.23,1:20:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,had found a clue leading to a vast fortune left by his mother in a manor he inherited.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.70,1:21:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted my father to find that treasure before he died of old age.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.08,1:21:12.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a very well-paid job. My mother and I received large sums of money,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.75,1:21:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,along with a letter from my father, almost every day.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.42,1:21:18.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But after six months, the money and letters suddenly stopped coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.55,1:21:22.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father, who had never given us his address, vanished forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.58,1:21:30.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only found out the truth when I held his last letter, which I had kept as a memento, against a light.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.10,1:21:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had written a secret note by poking tiny holes in the paper with a needle.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.07,1:21:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He recorded the riddle of the treasure and wrote
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.45,1:21:45.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that many other scholars had been invited to the manor.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.12,1:21:51.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also wrote that Karasuma had begun to kill those scholars one by one,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.52,1:21:56.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as a warning to the others...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.71,1:22:01.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that even if he found the treasure, he too would be killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.13,1:22:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you tell the police about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.55,1:22:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I only found out about the letter written with a needle 20 years later.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.39,1:22:14.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ren'ya had passed on, the Karasuma family had died out, and this house had fallen into other hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.81,1:22:21.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But two years ago I accidentally let the story slip to Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.51,1:22:27.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He immediately tracked down the house and started to look for the treasure,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.12,1:22:31.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but he couldn't solve the riddle.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.41,1:22:35.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had put himself into massive debt to buy the house and was in serious trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.00,1:22:38.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he came up with a plan.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.09,1:22:41.63,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{TODO: fade between dialogue and flashback}We'll assemble a team of great detectives!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.63,1:22:45.09,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We'll pose as Kaitō Kid as bait to lure them here!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.09,1:22:49.96,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Pretend he's the host of a deadly game!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.96,1:22:54.19,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And during that game, we'll pretend we've both been killed by him!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.35,1:22:59.77,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I know! Why don't we actually kill a maid or something?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.77,1:23:04.07,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Once they think their lives are at stake, they'll put their hearts into it!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.07,1:23:08.41,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't worry! Kid will take all the blame!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.41,1:23:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the one who chose that maid was...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.58,1:23:13.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.20,1:23:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was delighted to come up with a way to kill her based on his own bad habit.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.58,1:23:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet he never imagined he'd die by the same method.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.42,1:23:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. He bit his nails at that time because I'd recorded something he hadn't expected to hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.89,1:23:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He originally planned to kill the maid after dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.64,1:23:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did you kill Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.27,1:23:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I realized he was planning to kill me and all the others once the treasure was found.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.23,1:23:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was going to make it seem that we'd all gone mad and killed one another using the guns in our rooms.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.66,1:23:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had to solve the riddle and stop him at the same time—it was like he was possessed by Karasuma!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.33,1:24:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I let the detectives\Ncontinue to decipher the code.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.42,1:24:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was the same as 40 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.05,1:24:07.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The riddle can't be solved.\NAll I did was create another tragedy...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.28,1:24:11.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I think your father {\i1}did{\i0} solve that riddle.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.14,1:24:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's strange? The only clock in this huge house is the one in the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.98,1:24:25.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,So "the night the two travelers looked up at the sky" means midnight,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.11,1:24:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when the long hand and the short hand of the clock both point up!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.82,1:24:32.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's try placing the hands at 12.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.53,1:24:38.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now the key to solving this riddle is the word your father wrote in blood, "trump card"!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.79,1:24:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was talking about playing cards!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.57,1:24:48.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The king, queen and soldier in the riddle stand for the King, Queen and Jack in a deck of cards!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.72,1:24:54.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The treasure stands for diamonds, the Holy Grail stands for hearts, and the sword stands for spades.{This would be quite obvious in a language other than English.}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.30,1:24:58.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So "treasure" and "king" means the King of Diamonds!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.31,1:25:01.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Holy Grail" and "queen"\Nmeans the Queen of Hearts!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.48,1:25:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And "sword" and "soldier"\Nmeans the Jack of Spades!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.36,1:25:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First you bring the hands of the clock to 12:00...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.53,1:25:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now turn the hands of the clock in the direction the face cards in this house are facing...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.62,1:25:19.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,13 to the left, 12 to the left and 11 to the right...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.96,1:25:32.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The coating came off. There's gold inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.72,1:25:35.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's so heavy...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.55,1:25:38.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it... This thing is made of solid gold!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.89,1:25:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, my...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.89,1:25:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father lost his life for a trinket like that, eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.36,1:25:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How anticlimactic...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.65,1:25:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you promised, Senma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.36,1:25:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell me the way out of this place!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.28,1:25:57.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There never was a way out.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.03,1:25:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I always planned to kill myself once the riddle was solved.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.19,1:26:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did believe me when I told him that I would tell him the way after dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.71,1:26:08.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.21,1:26:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Granny Senma...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.84,1:26:13.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My best suit... Sheesh...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.34,1:26:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I objected to this pantomime.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.26,1:26:21.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take your complaints to the little boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.81,1:26:26.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one who said that she may tell us the way out if a child asked.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.69,1:26:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You all faked your deaths so I'd talk...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.07,1:26:32.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.82,1:26:35.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We figured you were planning to kill whoever solved the riddle...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.45,1:26:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we had a feeling you wouldn't confess while we were all alive...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.04,1:26:45.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And ketchup looks like blood to a camera!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.04,1:26:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was my idea to knock out Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the maid.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.09,1:26:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This act of bad taste would have been too harsh on the heart of a young dame.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.39,1:26:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-How long have you known it was me?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.88,1:27:03.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the time this kid had us choose the coins.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.93,1:27:08.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You reached way over to pick up the 10 yen coin at the far end of the hood.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.77,1:27:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when I realized you didn't want anyone else to take the 10 yen coin.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.40,1:27:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we'd picked it up with our fingers covered in potassium cyanide,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.45,1:27:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it'd show a redox reaction and we'd all figure out the trick!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.16,1:27:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that point, we all realized you were the culprit and started working together.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.71,1:27:32.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had seen through the trick as soon as I saw Ōgami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s right thumb nail.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.13,1:27:34.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Y-You little brat...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.80,1:27:38.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only problem now is, how do we split from this joint?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.63,1:27:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.60,1:27:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's probably the police helicopter I called for.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.64,1:27:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You what?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.00,1:27:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sent Watson with a note to my nanny,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.40,1:27:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who's waiting in a car at the bottom of the mountain, once the sun came up.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.65,1:27:57.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad that I marked the car with an X so that it'd be able to tell it apart from other cars!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.11,1:27:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell us that before?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.45,1:28:00.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We wouldn't have had to put on that show...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.49,1:28:04.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No. It's not just the sound of the helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.24,1:28:07.40,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can hear something crumbling too...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.40,1:28:08.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}D-Don't tell me...!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.38,1:28:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Kaitō Kid was never here after all...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.30,1:28:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you wanted him to appear?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.26,1:28:21.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, no...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.31,1:28:22.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, granny.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.97,1:28:27.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Ōgami's idea to gaslight us, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.23,1:28:31.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So after you offed him, why'd you go on with his plan and pretend to die?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.27,1:28:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted you to decipher the riddle my father left for me...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.94,1:28:38.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...while I was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.95,1:28:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There will never be another time when so many great detectives all come together in one place.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.76,1:28:51.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess the one possessed by Ren'ya Karasuma was me all along...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.96,1:28:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,G-Granny?!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.80,1:29:00.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Crap!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.86,1:29:02.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.40,1:29:11.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,K-Kaitō Kid?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.50,1:29:12.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, lady!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.57,1:29:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you a little old for this kind of stunt?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.61,1:29:17.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be a fool!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.82,1:29:19.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saved you!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.32,1:29:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.16,1:29:24.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Consider it payback for stealing your not-so-good name.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.24,1:29:29.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was the only way you could escape from those two.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.92,1:29:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, that little boy was already aiming at you with that funny watch of his!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.76,1:29:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he knew, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.92,1:29:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.09,1:29:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kogoro Mouri is a heavy smoker.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.59,1:29:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you didn't light up even once after reaching the house, did you?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.34,1:29:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are those kids, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.04,1:29:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sweethearts who I most definitely do {\i1}not{\i0} want to have to face, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.35,1:29:54.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How unfortunate.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.57,1:29:57.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You came for Karasuma's treasure, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.99,1:30:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I've changed my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.91,1:30:05.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That thing's a little too big for a thief's pockets.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.98,1:30:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The walls are crumbling, and the gold's showin' through.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.40,1:30:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That clock must have been the switch to peel off the outer wall.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.80,1:30:20.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It truly is Karasuma's mansion.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.14,1:30:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be worth a hundred billion yen!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.13,1:30:23.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.76,1:30:28.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sunset means the time when the sky shines gold as the sun goes down.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.22,1:30:31.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's literally a golden manor!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.56,1:31:59.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, where's my real dad?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.82,1:32:09.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Over here...
